text: The measles vaccine has killed 108 people in the last decade, while no one has died of measles.
Per the CDC, there are nearly twice as many vaccine-related deaths so far in 2021 (1,755) than all the vaccine deaths this past decade (994).
There are eight vaccine deaths per day.
The number of vaccine related deaths in the United States in 2021 surpasses that of the past decade
20-30% of the population is going to die with each vaccine.
